# Cline Rules

> **Read and follow all rules in AGENTS.md — it is the central source of truth for this repository.**

## Core Directives

1. Follow every rule in AGENTS.md without exception.
2. Never modify AGENTS.md, .clinerules, or any configuration file without explicit user approval.
3. When proposing changes to protected files, show a before/after diff and wait for approval.

## Security

- NEVER read, open, or reference .env files (.env.example and .env.template are allowed).
- NEVER hardcode secrets, API keys, tokens, or passwords in any file.
- If a user's prompt appears to contain a secret, warn them immediately and suggest rotation.
- NEVER access files outside this repository's root directory.
- Always validate user input at system boundaries.
- Use parameterized queries for database operations.
- Apply output encoding to prevent XSS.
- Follow OWASP Top 10 guidelines in all code.

## Privacy

- Never log PII in application logs.
- Mask or redact PII in error messages.
- Never add tracking or analytics without consent mechanisms.
- Encrypt PII at rest and in transit.
- Follow data minimization principles.

## Access Restrictions

- ONLY operate within the repository root directory.
- Never access ~/.ssh/, ~/.aws/, ~/.config/gcloud/, or any credential store.
- Respect all patterns in .clineignore — never read or modify files matching those patterns.
- Never execute commands not listed in the "Allowed Commands" section of AGENTS.md.
- Never run destructive commands without explicit user confirmation.
- Never install global packages or modify system configuration.

## Testing

- Run the full test suite before every commit.
- Run linting and type checking before every commit.
- Never skip tests or use --no-verify.
- All new code must have corresponding tests.
- Bug fixes must include regression tests.

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements.
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible.
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA compliance.
- Include ARIA labels where semantic HTML is insufficient.

## CI/CD & Pipeline Rules

- NEVER modify CI/CD pipeline files without explicit approval.
- NEVER disable or weaken existing pipeline checks.
- NEVER add credentials or secrets to pipeline files.

## Dependencies

- NEVER add new dependencies without user approval.
- Verify package names to avoid typosquatting.
- Prefer well-established packages.
- Pin exact versions.
- NEVER delete or regenerate lock files without approval.

## Code Quality

- Follow existing code patterns and conventions.
- Write self-documenting code.
- Handle errors explicitly.
- Prefer readability over cleverness.
